Barcelona have announced their squad to face Sevilla in the La Liga on Sunday at Camp Nou. Barcelona coach, Ernesto Valverde, released a 19-man squad to tackle Sevilla on the club’s official website on Saturday. Barcelona head to the game following a 2-0 victory over Getafe in the La Liga last week. Below is Barcelona squad: Ter Stegen, Semedo, Pique, Rakitic, Sergio, Todibo, Arthur, Suarez, Messi, Dembele, Neto, Griezmann, Jordi Alba, Roberto, De Jong, Vidal, Perez, Ansu Fati, Araujo. The kick-off time for the match is 8pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.